rComments: Mandatory attendance, assigns a 5 page paper that we only had a weekend to do. If you're working a side job and have other homework intensive classes, good luck.

Professor Jones is hands down one of the best teachers at UCSC. She is SO smart, funny and man, she pushes you more than any teacher! A LOT of work, not easy class, but her teaching, helpfulness and passion for what she does makes this class WORTH your money. She's the best, and will challenge you to do your best. Great teacher.
Jones is a great professor but is a tough grader. The TA was not much help for the final take home exam. Rather than having helpful discussions, we just sat there in silence.

She is such a lovely professor. The books were all interesting, but some of the articles were a little dense or dry. She is super understanding and very easy to talk to. She organized lectures in a pretty effective way. Overall, she's an awesome prof that hist people should take at some point. You do a lot better than you think if you participate.

I have had her twice and hope to have her as much as possible during my time at ucsc.  she is the most inspirational teacher/professor/lecturer I have ever met.  She wants all her students to do well and has a never ending supply of knowledge to offer them.  I cannot emphasize how much I love her!!!

Dr. Jones is a fantastic professor. Her knowledge of the material is extensive and she is extremely helpful and approachable. Her lectures are very dense but they are really interesting and you'll gain a lot from them. Lecture is mandatory-you will fall behind if you miss even one class- and her tests are challenging, but she's a great teacher.

simply the best and most brilliant up and coming professor at UCSC. If you love history, you will love her--she is a focused, funny lecturer and she posts an enormity of notes and test preparation online just for you. I could not ask for more in a professor, this woman is incredibly dedicated. Had her for (2) classes so far.

Loved this class. Dr. Jones does a great job covering a lot of material in the amount of time there is.  There's about 150 pages of reading per week but it's all really interesting and relates well to the lectures.  Jones is helpful and funny. Only two essays, five pages min each. Midterm and final are straightforward and doable if you study.

Professor Jones is super nice and really knowledgable.  Sometimes her lectures get borderline dry and boring, but then she throws in a funny comment or an interesting fact and pulls them back on track.  It's important to attend lecture to do well, even though it's not mandatory.  The exams are difficult if you don't pay attention.
Awesome professor.... Always engaged and encouraging in discussion. She listens well and lectures well-she is brilliant and nice. I cannot wait to take her again!
